&lt;p&gt;We are currently seeking to recruit an enthusiastic Community Practice Teacher Health Visiting to join the Aylesbury Health Visiting Team based at Stoke Mandeville Hospital Aylesbury. &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;This is an exciting opportunity for you to join us and share your valuable skills, knowledge and leadership qualities.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;We welcome appilcations from all qualified Health Visitor Community Practice Teachers . &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;The teams consist of Health Visitors, Community Staff Nurses and Community Nursery Nurses under the management of a Locality Lead.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;You will participate in leading your team of skill mix staff, with a public health focus and be fully committed to improving the health and well being of the local population. Your responsibilities will include staff support, supervision, appraisal and student learning.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;You will have the opportunity to contribute to the development of joint working with Children’s Centres and the implementation of the Healthy Child Programme within the Solihull Approach model of working.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;You will receive regular restorative clinical supervision and child protection supervision, with access to excellent internal and external training.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;You must be a registered SCPHN (Health Visiting) and Community Practice Teacher with current NMC registration.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Jenny Chapman, Operational Lead&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Email address : jennychapman1@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Telephone number : 07876391217&lt;/p&gt;
